<br>
No it's not, it's a well known debate that it works even when resisted. It could very well be that the additional time between nukes due to casting concussion and the recast is enough for your agro to decay enough to keep you from being #1 on the agro list.<br>
<br>
Try this some time on a mob that likes to resist concussion. Rather than casting concussion, count out the amount of time you would have spend casting it and waiting for refresh between nukes, you will get the very same results as casting a resisted concussion. I have tried it and I don't believe for one minute that concussion works when it is resisted.<br>
<br>
If concussion was meant to work even when resisted, why bother giving it a resist check???<br>
<br>
Everyone is getting worked up because ONE person thinks they are getting unusual agro. If crits = agro, where are all of the other wizards complaining about all this agro we are supposed to be getting? Settle down and wait for more people to chime in with their opinions. Better yet, log in and try it yourself before running around like chicken little.<br>
<br>
I suppose the new list of patch posts should be jboots are nerfed, there are more resists, and crits cause extra agro. <p><div align="center" class="font-size: 11px; font-family: arial">
